cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.DL 

The paper discusses the analysis of the structure of content-based clusters and communities on the Web using a topic taxonomy and an automatic classifier. This falls under the domain of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Search Engines (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of random walk algorithms and link-based ranking systems, which are relevant to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The analysis of textual properties of nodes and the use of topic taxonomies are also relevant to Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL).
